dataIdInfo.idPurp: Administrative boundary lines for South Sudan admin level 0-2, Abyei boundaries and disputed borders. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent. These lines can be helpful for cartographic purposes

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was created by ITOS by converting the South Sudan Admin2 polygon layer to lines and integrating Abyei boundary lines and disputed border lines. The lines were created after all processing on the admin layer had been completed by ITOS.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in. A -1 value has been included for disputed boundaries.
